entries.name: Telit
entries.description:
Telit is the global leader in Internet of Things (IoT) enablement. We offer the industrys broadest portfolio of integrated products, platforms and services to support and enable IoT deployments from things to apps. Our portfolio of modules addresses all cellular communication technologies, GNSS and short-to-long range wireless applications. Our IoT connectivity plans and IoT platform services help reduce the risks, time to market, complexity and costs associated with deploying and providing IoT services across industries and vertical markets worldwide.

Telit started as module provider for GSM GPRS connectivity and evolved over time up to LTE now, they also cover GPS/GLNS positioning and short range wireless.

They have recently started providing device management and IoT cloud operations - apparently in cooperation with AWS and SAP - as well as FOTA firmware updates - it seems based on Red Bend solutions.

They offer a wide range of development boards in addition to the ready-made production modules.

They have expanded in design services, certification and training as well.

Close to 900 employees world-wide.

As you can find in the 2016 FY fiscal results (http://www.telit.com/fileadmin/investor_news_downloads/final-031317-telit-full-year-2016-financial-results-13650440__002_.pdf), they have been growing double digit % for the seventh year in a row and reached $370M (+11%), they are profitable with $32.8M before tax (+18.4%).

Strong partnership with NXP especially for automotive and security. They acquired NXP Automotive Telematics Unit in 2014.

Interesting list of partners incl. Intel, Qualcomm, CSR, Micron.

Registered offices and Global HQ in London, CEO HQ in Rome and R&D in Trieste (North East Italy). Technical support and product development everywhere worldwide: Releigh (NC), Sao Paulo (Brazil) and Seoul (Korea).

I have just established successful contact with the R&D Director in Italy, Antonino Sgroio, responsible for all cellular modules. He has accepted to receive our deck and have a call with me and possibly later a face to face meeting.

(I am also trying to approach their EVP of Products & Solutions and Head of Global R&D in Geneva)

I would pitch our value proposition to Telit as:

- LITE membership for the client side -> drive the requirements for the network protocols with Zephyr, the exec environment and scripting languages, integration to cloud services. test cases, get full ownership of the sw stack in their products, fully open source, free from royalties or commercial agreements

- 96Boards -> open source software reference images and support on Telit 96B IoT development platform, leverage our tech team for their developers, focus on their value add for design and consulting business on product solutions

entries.name: SECO
entries.description:
SECO (IOT.MI), listed on Borsa Italianas Mercato Telematico Azionario (STAR segment), is a center of excellence in the field of innovation and technological integration. The company has been operating in the high tech market for over 40 years, designing, developing and manufacturing cutting-edge proprietary technological solutions for industrial clients.

SECO products range from miniaturized computers to standard or customized hardware, high-tech finished products and hardware-software integrated systems for highly diversified end-markets, including medical, industrial automation, aerospace and defense, wellness and vending systems. In addition, the company has further improved its product range with the launch of Clea, a proprietary Platform as A Service (i.e. PaaS), providing services and solutions for applications within the Internet of Things (IoT) allowing clients to manage their IoT Endpoints in an efficient, effective and simple manner.

SECO operates on a global scale with offices in Europe, North America, and Asia, as well as production facilities in Italy and China, serving more than 200 blue-chip customers which are leaders in their respective fields. SECO R&D capabilities are further enhanced by long-lasting strategic partnerships with tech giants and collaboration with universities, research centers, and innovative start-ups. SECO is an investee of FITEC, managed by Fondo Italiano d'Investimento SGR.
